node.text:
Sometimes we want to believe things even though we know they're not real.. Perhaps the biggest disease of our age is the disappearance of real emotions.. Sometimes we feel the need to be loved, to feel someone's compassion.. And sometimes we want to believe in the "moment" we're experiencing despite knowing it's not real.. It was a "moment" like this that had its effect on me today.. A moment that I wanted to believe to be real, but then accepted to be not.. Even if it was for a very short amount of time, the effect of that moment when I felt beautiful, when I felt like I was in a dream, made me compose this.. Being happy for a short time, daydreaming, and then admitting that what you want is impossible...

(The recording is bad, the sound is bad, but it's an important composition for me.. That's why I wanted to share it with you..)

Warning! Graphic content starting with the 6th photo! 
I’ve been typing and deleting this for hours, thinking about what to write, how to explain this.. Just yesterday I shared a cat that I ran into with you.. Less than a day later, we met this child while we were outside feeding the cats in the neighbourhood at 4 am. I cried so much at his state, I was so upset.. He only weighs 650 grams.. His mouth and teeth have basically melted.. Who knows how long he’s been like this, for how long he hasn’t eaten.. 😔 I though he passed away while we were on the way to the veterinary.. 😔 All the emergency interventions were made, all the necessary blood work is done, and we began his treatment.. As you can see his situation is not very good, but I’m remaining hopeful as always, I want to believe that he will survive.. I hope we will all witness a miracle together.. For those of you that have been asking about the cat from yesterday’s post; his state is better today compared to yesterday however his life is unfortunately still under threat. I will keep updating you on that.. This year I am struggling physically, financially, and psychologically but of course I will not give up.. Right now there are 3 cats with kidney disease, 3 fip, and a total of 8 ill cats including these new 2 ones.. It gets really difficult to keep up with all of them when it happens this back to back.. I would highly appreciate it for them if you could show your support 🙏
You can use the patreon link on my profile.. And send them your good energies so they can get better 🙏🌸💙

node.text:
Me and this beautiful boy ran into each other approximately 4 hours ago while I was on a walk.. I noticed that something was wrong with him as soon as I saw him. He looked very exhausted, his breathing wasn’t good and his body temperature was way too high.. He is such a calm and loving cat that even though I didn’t have a cat box with me, he didn’t react at all when I picked him up and he didn’t get scared in the car.. It was like he knew we wanted to help him.. 😔 We immediately took him to the veterinary and the results are unfortunately quite bad 😔 Feline panleukopenia positive.. Coronavirus is also positive.. His blood work came back quite awful as well.. His fever is 41.3 degrees.. 
The veterinary doctors immediately started his treatments. I know his chance of surviving is low but I’m remaining hopeful. After his fever dropped a little with the treatments he started to eat 🙏🧿🌸 Please don’t forget to send him your good energies… 💙
(If you want to support my fight for them, you can use the link in my profile 🙏 )
.
"Bu güzel çocukla yaklaşık 4 saat önce yürüyüş yaparken karşılaştık.. Görür görmez bir problem olduğunu farkettim, çok halsiz görünüyordu, solunumu kötüydü ve vücut sıcaklığı çok yüksekti.. O kadar sakin, o kadar sevecen bir kedi ki, yanımda kedi boxı yoktu ama kucağıma aldığım an hiç tepki vermedi, arabada hiç korkmadı.. Ona yardım etmek istediğimizi biliyor gibiydi.. 😔 Hemen veterinere gittik, maalesef sonuçlar çok kötü 😔 Feline panleukopenia pozitif çıktı.. Corona zaten pozitif.. Ve kan değerleri çok kötü maalesef.. Ateşi de 41.3 derece
.. Hemen tedavisine başlandı. Yaşama şansı düşük bunu biliyorum ama umudumu kaybetmiyorum.. Tedavilerle ateşi biraz düşünce yemek yemeye başladı 🙏🧿🌸 Onun için güzel enerjilerinizi göndermeyi unutmayın... 💙"

I come bearing great news! 😊 Remember Cookie? I first made a post about him on May 6th. Unfortunately, he was diagnosed with neurological Fip.. He also had a serious amount of fluid accumulated in his stomach 😔 You can check his initial state from the photo I shared on May 6th. His treatment took about 100 days and now Cookie has defeated Fip entirely and clung to life! I'm so happy.. Even though Cookie doesn't seem to be very happy in the photos, I very much am 🙄😅 Even though it may seem ordinary, it's actually such a big deal that he beat Fip! Thank you to everyone who supported Cookie. When you get injections for 100 days, you can only smile so much in photos 🙄😅❤ If you want to help support the other cats that are still under treatment, you can use the link in my profile..
.
"Size harika bir haberle geldim! 😊Cookie'yi hatırlıyor musunuz? ilk olarak 6 mayısta paylaşmıştım. Nörolojik Fip hastasıydı maalesef.. Ayrıca karnında da ciddi oranda sıvı birikmişti 😔 İlk halini 6 mayıstaki gönderiden kontrol edebilirsiniz. Yaklaşık 100 gün sürdü tedavisi ve artık Cookie de Fip'i tamamen yendi ve hayata tutundu! O kadar mutluyum ki.. Cookie pek öutlu görünmese de fotoğraflarda ben çok mutluyum 🙄😅Sıradan gibi görünse de Fip'i yenmesi öyle büyük birşey ki! Cookie'ye destek olan herkese çok teşekkür ederim. 100 gün boyunca iğne olunca fotoğraflarda en fazla bu kadar gülümseyebiliyor 🙄😅❤"

node.text:
Yesterday, I shared with you that Hamdi, one of the cats being treated for fip, has recovered. Let me give you other good news, I found him a home! He won't be returning to the streets anymore 😊🙏
We changed Hamdi's life with your support.. 😊 But Fip treatment for the other cats continues.. Especially the last black cat I found.. He is being administered a very high dosage due to being an advanced case.. Each of these bottles you see costs 120 dollars.. And for the remaining treatments, we need about 80 more bottles.. Today we ordered 50 more bottles.. I know I exhausted you a lot this year, but I'm really having a hard time keeping up.. I wish the meds weren't so expensive and the treatment didn't last 84 days that I wouldn't have to ask for your support 😔 I pondered for a while before posting this, cuz I'm really ashamed to ask for your support, but I can't keep up with it all alone 😔 If you want to support us, you can use the link on my profile 🙏🌸 I'm posting this with many apologies..

node.text:
I have great news for you! I first posted about Hamdi on May 11th!You can check out the post on may 11th 🙂 His 84-day Fip treatment is all done and we beat Fip!!! I'm oh so happy for him. Maybe there are some of you that know of this disease. Until about 2 years ago, all the cats diagnosed with FIP were being euthanized because there used to be no cure. Yea, the meds are quite expensive, but it's like a miracle to see them survive! Hamdi made it thanks to your help.. Thank you all soooo so much.. And Hamdi's appetite is also great! He's continuously gaining weight 🙄😅 I hope I'll find him a good home now.. I hope that, together, we'll see the other cats that're being treated for Fip get better as well 🙏🙂 What did we say? Love heals.. ❤😊🌸
.
Sizlere harika bir haberim var ! Hamdiyi ilk olarak 11 mayısta paylaşmıştım sizlerle! 84 günlük Fip tedavisi bitti ve Fipi yendik!!! O kadar mutluyum ki onun için. Belki bilenler vardır bu hastalığı. Bundan 2 sene öncesine kadar fip hastası tüm kedilere ötenazi yapılıyordu çaresi olmadığı için. Evet ilaçlar çok pahalı ama hayatta kaldıklarını görmek mucize gibi! Hamdi sizin destekleriniz sayesinde yaşadı.. Hepinize çok ama çoook teşekkür ederim.. Ve Hamdi'nin iştahı da harika! Sürekli kilo alıyor 🙄😅 Şimdi ona güzel bir yuva bulmamız lazım! 84 gün tedavi görüp Fipi atlattıktan sonra sokaklara dönmesin 🙏🙂 Sahiplenmek isteyen bana mesaj atsın lütfen. Artık hiçbir sağlık sorunu yok 🙏😊 İç dış parazitlerini de yaptırdım, evde yaşamaya tamamen hazır 😊 Tedavisi devam eden diğer Fipli kedilerimizin de iyileştiğini göreceğiz umarım hep beraber 🙏🙂  Ne demiştik? Sevgi iyileştirir.. ❤😊🌸

node.text:
I can't share what I see with you, though I respect those who do.. I know that there are many people with good hearts who follow this page, and if they see what I see, maybe they will be devastated like me; with the helplessness of not being able to do anything, they may never, not for a minute, find the strength to stand up.. There is a need for the strength of good people in this disgusting world.. All I can say to you is that everything is worse and more painful than we thought.. And there is incredible chaos.. Those who were supposed to work towards putting out the fires didn't do what was necessary; maybe they didn't wanna do it, I don't know. That's why we tried desperately to help, but failed on many fronts. Maybe millions of animals, millions of trees burned.. I'm trying to do whatever I can and I will continue to do so but we aren't able to do much.. Many people from other countries ask if we are okay; we are the way one can be in a country where millions of animals have been burning alive for days.. I'll try to provide all the help I can for the animals that were affected from the fires and made it out alive and wounded..
.
"Gördüklerimi sizlerle paylaşamıyorum, paylaşanlara saygı duyuyorum.. Biliyorum ki bu sayfayı takip eden güzel kalpli çok insan var, ve benim gördüklerimi görürlerse belki benim gibi kahrolacaklar, ellerinden birşey gelmemesinin çaresizliğiyle birdaha hiçbir zaman, hiçbir dakika ayağa kalkacak güç bulamayacaklar.. Güzel insanların gücüne çok ihtiyaç var bu iğreç dünyada.. Size tek söyleyebileceğim herşey düşündüğümüzden de daha kötü, daha acı.. Ve inanılmaz bir kaos var.. Bu yangına asıl müdahale etmesi gerekenler, gereken şeyleri yapmadı, belki de yapmak istemedi bilmiyorum. O yüzden bizler çaresizce yardım etmeye çalıştık ama yetemedik birçok şeye. Belki milyonlarca hayvan, milyonlarca ağaç yandı.. Elimden geleni yapmaya çalışıyorum ve yapmaya çalışacağım ama yetemiyoruz hiçbir şeye.. Diğer ülkelerden soran çok oluyor iyi misiniz diye; milyonlarca hayvanın günlerdir diri diri yandığı bir ülkede nasıl olunursa öyleyiz.. Yangından etkilenen ve sağ kalan, yaralı tüm hayvanlar için elimden gelen her yardımı yapmaya çalışacağım.."

I've come across so many injured animals this year that I haven't been able to share them all with you.. I saw the yellow cat in front of a cafe 2 weeks ago. He seemed to be in really bad condition.. I took him to the vet immediately.. Unfortunately, his mouth is in very bad condition, but what's even worse are his kidneys..  We're guessing he's over 10 years old. He will probably be treated at the clinic for months.. Once his kidneys are stable, I'll look for a home for him so that he doesn't live in a cage, but in a home instead. If you want to adopt him, please send me a message 🙏

.

I met the 3-colored cat while feeding strays last week. Unfortunately, she seems to have eaten wall barley.. Her mouth and kidneys are in a very bad state.. She is about 2 years old; that's why there is a better chance of recovery 😔 But because of her kidneys, she will need treatment for quite a long time.. There are currently 9 cats being treated at the vet along with these two children. And I need your support.. If you wanna help them, you can use the link on my profile 🙏💙 I'll be sharing updates..

LÜTFEN OKUR MUSUNUZ?
.
Belki sırası değil ama biz bu insanlara, kurumlara gereken tepkiyi vermedikçe hiçbir zaman bitmeyecekler.. Bugün akşam 19.00 civarı kız arkadaşımla kuzguncukta yürürken "Klas Köfte" isimli bu mekanın sahibi dükkanın önündeki yavru kediyi 4 defa ayağıyla iteledi, tekmeler gibi uzaklaştırmaya çalıştı. Gözümüzün önünde olunca kız arkadaşım "napıyorsun" diyerek tepki verdi. Ben de "napıyorsunuz, niye tekmeliyorsunuz" diyip kediyi kucağıma alıp kenara koydum. Ardından resimlerde görülen dükkan sahibi hakaret etmeye başladı, ardından bir anda diğer esnafla birlikte 7-8 kişi üzerimize yürüdüler, 2 kişi el kaldırarak hakaretler etmeye devam ettiler. Araya girenler olsa da biz gidene kadar hakaret ve tehditlere devam ettiler.. Yanımda sadece kız arkadaşım varken 7-8 kişi üzerime yürüyüp iteleyip hakaretler ettiler. Erkeklik bu çünkü onlara göre.. Şimdi ben gidip bunların dükkanını başına yıksam bu devlet beni suçlu sayacak biliyorsunuz. Sizden ricam bu mekana gitmeyin, ve lütfen bana güveniyorsanız gereken tepkiyi gösterin 🙏 Google'da, yemeksepetinde, nerede isterseniz tepkinizi göstermenizi, ve insanların haberdar olması için paylaşmanızı rica ediyorum. Sizden ilk defa böyle birşey istiyorum.. Bu hayvan düşmanı işletmelere bu ülkede başka türlü tepki gösterirsek biz suçlu oluyoruz maalesef.. Google'a "Kuzguncuk Klas Köfte" yazarsanız direk çıkıyor..

node.text:
Hi everyone! I wanted to share the latest updates on the cats that are being treated for FIP. 😊
.
I had shared about the cat in the first video on May 27th. He's on the 47nd day of his treatment. And honestly, we think he's completely out of the life threatening stage now. His balance and general condition are also much better than his original state. 😊
.
I had shared about the cat in the second video on May 11th. He's on the 69rd day of treatment. His balance is almost all good now. His general condition is very good as well 😊
.
I had shared about the cat in the third video on May 6th. He's on the 73th day. His general condition and balance are very good. 😊
.
I shared about the cat in the fourth video 16 days ago. It has been 16 days since his treatment started. It takes a longer time to see the effect of the drug. And frankly, this child has the most severe FIP case I've ever come across. Unfortunately, his condition is very advanced. But I'm hopeful as he's still alive and is not getting worse. 🙏
.
I'm sharing the empty medication bottles in the last photo. For the remaining treatments, approximately 3 times this amount of medication will be used..
.
During the treatment, cats unfortunately get aggressive and frightened as they are given injections every day, kept in the cage all the time and need frequent blood tests. That's why they're so scared in the videos. Although it's a very expensive and difficult treatment process, I'm incredibly happy to see that they are getting better.. We really need your support during the rest of their treatment process. If you do wanna help, you can use the link in my profile. Please don't forget to send them your good vibes. 🙏😊

node.text: Today is my birthday and a person from a completely different part of the world, from a completely different country, sent this email at exactly midnight in Turkey.. I was really touched. I don't know who you are, but thank you so much.. Thank you so much for thinking about doing this, and for waiting for this exact hour to send me that email. Thank you as well to everyone else who sent me messages. There were those who wanted to send me a birthday gift. If you wanted to gift me something, the best present for me would be to help support the 4 cats that are currently being treated for Fip. If you wanna support their fight to survive, you can use the link in my profile. I can't believe I turned 32 🤦🏻‍♂️ 😂 Thanks for all your kind wishes 😊🙏
